The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, August 01, 2003 				 Wanted MP
																								Patna, July 31: As many as 12 ruling RJD legislators tonight submitted a memorandum to Bihar chief minister Rabri Devi asking her to rescind the order of the state police chief arrest controversial party MP Mohammad Shahabuddin.																								The MLAs move came as the police were gearing up to arrest the MP who is facing several criminal cases.																								But Shahabuddin said over phone from Delhi: Whichever political boss is instigating the director-general of police to arrest me will suffer heavy political loss. As a law-abiding citizen, I will knock at the door of the judiciary for justice. Without naming him, the MP hinted that Laloo Prasad Yadav was behind the arrest order.
